    "content": "Filled with a caustic mixture that discharges when stepped on, these tetrahedral caltrops present a much more dangerous hazard than their mundane variety. A typical bag of these 1-inch health and safety nightmares contains [i]20 caltroozes[/i]. Small bubbles of acid forming and bursting inside the [i]caltroozes[/i] cause them to roll and shift.\r\n[b][i]Caltrops.[/i][/b] As an action, you can spread a single bag of [i]caltroozes[/i] to cover a [b]5-foot square[/b]. Any creature that enters the area must succeed on a [b]DC 15 Dexterity saving throw[/b] or stop moving and take [b]1[/b] piercing damage. Until the creature regains at least [b]1[/b] hit point, its walking speed is reduced by [b]10 feet.[/b] A creature that moves through the area of the caltroozes at half speed makes the saving throw against them with [b]advantage[/b].\r\n\r\n[b][i]Corrosive Chaos.[/i][/b] If a creature fails the Dexterity saving throw, roll a d4 and consult the table below to determine what additional effects take place:\r\n\r\n[table][tr][th]d4[/th][th]Effect[/th][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]1[/td]\r\n[td]The acid in the [i]caltroozes[/i] discharges in a single burst. The creature takes an additional [b]6d6 [/b]acid damage.[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td]2[/td]\r\n[td]The acid takes on lubricating qualities. While the creature’s speed is reduced by the [i]caltroozes[/i], it must succeed on a [b]DC 15 Dexterity saving throw[/b] at the end of each of its turns or fall [b]prone[/b].[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td]3[/td]\r\n[td]The acid coats the creature’s feet, continuously eating away at them. While the creature’s speed is reduced by the [i]caltroozes[/i], it takes [b]1d4[/b] acid damage for every [b]5 feet[/b] it walks or climbs.[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td]4[/td]\r\n[td]The acid causes a creature’s feet to temporarily deform. While the creature’s speed is reduced by the [i]caltroozes[/i], it has [b]disadvantage [/b]on Dexterity saving throws.[/td]\r\n[/tr][/table]\r\nAfter a creature fails a saving throw against the caltroozes, they are emptied of acid, and you can’t use this property again until you spend [b]10 minutes[/b] decanting a phial of biomantic acid into all the caltrops. The [i]caltrooze[/i]s can still be used as regular caltrops that deal magical piercing damage.",
